   Presentation: Licensure in Illinois      A presentation on social work licensure in Illinois, given by Joel Rubin, Executive Director of NASW-IL, to MSW students of the Jane Addams College of Social Work on March 12, 2019.       Application Information   Steps to Licensure  National Association of Social Work – IL, Licensure Steps  For more information download » Licensure in Illinois: What You Need to Know  Application  Download the application and carefully read the instructions.  Certification of Education Form  Complete the applicant section of the Certification of Education form (two pages) then forward it to Ms. Hazel Brown who will complete the remaining sections. Please let her know if you prefer she contact you when it is ready for pick up or if you want it mailed to you.  Due to the shelter in place order, routine processing of education verification forms for licensure applications will resume on June 1, 2020.  Mailing Address  ATTN: Hazel Brown UIC Jane Addams College of Social Work 1040 W. Harrison St. (MC 309) 4th Floor, Suite 4329 Chicago, IL 60607  Email Address memi@uic.edu  Fax Number (312) 996-1852  Mail Application  Per application instructions, submit your application and fee payment to the Illinois Department of Financial and Professional Regulation (IDFPR).  Once the IDFPR processes your application they will send you a letter with information on how to proceed forward.  Additional Information  IDPFR Technical Assistance Unit: (217) 782-8556  Illinois Department of Financial and Professional Regulation  Association of Social Work Boards       Consider Becoming a School Social Worker          Alumni & Friends    Back to main content           Make a Gift Now    IGNITE Campaign: Make Your Impact    Where & How to Give    Connect & Engage     Update Your Information    What's New With You?    Engage With Students    Alumni & Friends Newsletter      Alumni Events & Awards     Award Nominations      Alumni Updates    LSW/LCSW Information        